**3. Calculate the Standard Molar Entropy of Sublimation (\(\Delta_{sub}S_{m}^{\ominus}\))**

The entropy of sublimation is the difference between the entropy of the gaseous product and the solid reactant:
\begin{equation}
\Delta_{sub}S_{m}^{\ominus} = S_{m}^{\ominus}(\ce{I_{2}(g)}) - S_{m}^{\ominus}(\ce{I_{2}(s)})
\end{equation}
We are given the standard molar entropies:
\begin{align*}
S_{m}^{\ominus}(\ce{I_{2}(s)}) &= 116.1\ \text{J¡¤mol}^{-1}¡¤\text{K}^{-1} \\
