**4. Calculate the Normal Sublimation Temperature (\(T_{sub}\))**

Now we substitute the calculated values of \(\Delta_{sub}H_{m}^{\ominus}\) and \(\Delta_{sub}S_{m}^{\ominus}\) into the formula for \(T_{sub}\):
\begin{equation}
T_{sub} = \frac{\Delta_{sub}H_{m}^{\ominus}}{\Delta_{sub}S_{m}^{\ominus}} = \frac{62400\ \text{J¡¤mol}^{-1}}{144.6\ \text{J¡¤mol}^{-1}¡¤\text{K}^{-1}}
